
1: Install TOMCAT on linux box
							
Step #1: Install Tomcat

1.1 Create a Linux machine // Ubuntu 20.X
Prereq: Install JAVA

1.2: down load the package --> google doneload Apache Tomcat --> Version 8
Copy the link address

cd /opt
wget https://dlcdn.apache.org/tomcat/tomcat-8/v8.5.81/bin/apache-tomcat-8.5.81.tar.gz
tar xzvf apache-tomcat-8.5.81.tar.gz
mv apache-tomcat-8.5.81 tomcat

cd tomcat
cd bin/
./startup.sh    ---> Tomcat started.

Enabling remote access
-------------------
cd /opt/tomcat
find / -name context.xml

/opt/tomcat/webapps/manager/META-INF/context.xml
/opt/tomcat/webapps/host-manager/META-INF/context.xml

Backup of the Orignal files:
cp -p /opt/tomcat/webapps/manager/META-INF/context.xml /opt/tomcat/webapps/manager/META-INF/context.xml_ORIG

cp -p /opt/tomcat/webapps/host-manager/META-INF/context.xml /opt/tomcat/webapps/host-manager/META-INF/context.xml_ORIG


vi /opt/tomcat/webapps/manager/META-INF/context.xml
vi /opt/tomcat/webapps/host-manager/META-INF/context.xml

Comment the below line over both the files:
--------------

<!--  <Valve className="org.apache.catalina.valves.RemoteAddrValve"
  allow="127\.\d+\.\d+\.\d+|::1|0:0:0:0:0:0:0:1" /> -->

Restarted Tomcat:
--------------

cd /opt/tomcat/bin
./shutdown.sh 
./startup.sh 

Create users:
vi /opt/tomcat/conf/tomcat-users.xml

Addd these Roles and users at the end of the file:
----------
<role rolename="manager-gui" />
<role rolename="manager-script" />
<role rolename="manager-jmx" />
<role rolename="manager-status" />
<user username="admin" password="admin" roles="manager-gui, manager-script, manager-jmx, manager-status" />
<user username="deployer" password="deployer" roles="manager-script" />
<user username="tomcat" password="s3cert" roles="manager-gui" />

Restarted Tomcat:
--------------
cd /opt/tomcat/bin
./shutdown.sh 
./startup.sh 
